Sentencas: Perovskite-spinel composite conductive ceramics are developed for solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) cathode contact layer.
Titulo: Novel perovskite-spinel composite conductive ceramics for SOFC cathode contact layer

Sentencas: The precursor of the composite materials includes micron-sized La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2 Fe0.8O3 (LSCF) perovskite particles coated by the reduced nano-sized Mn0.9Y0.1CO2O4 (MYC) spinel material, and then it is sintered in-situ to obtain perovskite-spinel composites.
Titulo: Novel perovskite-spinel composite conductive ceramics for SOFC cathode contact layer

Sentencas: The sintering activity of the composites is enhanced by using the reduced spinel powders.
Titulo: Novel perovskite-spinel composite conductive ceramics for SOFC cathode contact layer

Sentencas: The conductive performance of the composite materials is effectively improved due to the high conductivity of perovskite LSCF particles utilized.
Titulo: Novel perovskite-spinel composite conductive ceramics for SOFC cathode contact layer

Sentencas: Measured at 750 degrees C under constant current density of 400 mA/cm(2), after running 200 h, the area specific resistance (ASR) value of cathode contact layer remains relatively stable at around 5.4 m Omega cm(2).
Titulo: Novel perovskite-spinel composite conductive ceramics for SOFC cathode contact layer

Sentencas: The developed LSCF-MYC composite as cathode contact layer presents good bonding strength with both cathode and interconnection, and shows obviously low contact resistance and high stability.
Titulo: Novel perovskite-spinel composite conductive ceramics for SOFC cathode contact layer
